article.headline: Stetson 74, North Florida 64
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- Ridge Graham scored 15 points and pulled down 10 rebounds to lead Stetson to a 74-64 win over North Florida in Atlantic Sun play Saturday night. The Hatters (3-4, 1-1) fell behind 7-0, but tied the score at 11 with 13:19 to play in the opening half. There were seven ties and five lead changes over the rest of the half before North Florida took a 30-27 halftime lead. Stetson started the second half on a 14-4 run to take a 41-34 lead with 13:59 remaining in the game. With the score tied at 49 with 6:18 left, the Hatters used a 24-12 run -- capped off by two free throws from Aaron Graham -- to build their largest lead of the game, 73-61, with 16 seconds to play. Aaron Graham ended with a game-high 20 points, while Corey Walden added 15 for Stetson. Parker Smith had 13 points to lead the Ospreys (4-4, 1-1) -- who had their three-game winning streak snapped.
